HOUSE JOINT RESOLUTION 1406
By Powell
A RESOLUTION to honor and celebrate the Japan Men's National
Team for selecting the State of Tennessee and
Metropolitan Nashville to host its base camp and
training site for the 2026 World Cup.
WHEREAS, the members of this General Assembly are pleased to recognize a global
sporting event that will contribute significantly to Tennessee's economy while entertaining
soccer fans worldwide; and
WHEREAS, the Japan Men's National Team will use Nashville SC's Training Center in
Antioch as its team base camp and training site in preparation for the FIFA 2026 World Cup this
summer; and
WHEREAS, additionally, the Japanese Men's National Team and members of the Japan
Football Association delegation will reside in Nashville when they are not traveling to World Cup
host cities for matches; and
WHEREAS, spread across twelve acres and featuring 60,000 square feet of space,
Nashville SC's Training Center is a world-class, state-of-the-art soccer complex that is home to
three soccer fields, a full-service-dining hall, a theater-style video and film room, multiple cardio
and weight-training areas, cryogenic chambers to aid in athlete recovery, and on-site medical
facilities; and
WHEREAS, the Japanese Men's National Team's selection of Nashville for its 2026
World Cup base camp solidifies the Music City's reputation as a worldwide hub for soccer and
emphasizes the city's importance in the global soccer landscape; and
WHEREAS, there is also an important economic component to Nashville hosting a base
camp and training site for Japan, which is ranked 18th in the world by FIFA; and
HJR1406
017735
- 1 -

WHEREAS, according to an analysis prepared for San Antonio, Texas's World Cup
planning by Market Edge, non-host U.S. cities serving as an official FIFA training hub are
projected to generate between $5 million and $15 million from a base camp arrangement; and
WHEREAS, the University of Tennessee will play an important role in the success of the
first World Cup held on American soil since 1994; and
WHEREAS, because of its renowned turfgrass management program, the University of
Tennessee was selected by FIFA to create the best natural grass playing surfaces at all sixteen
host cities and dozens of training facilities across the U.S., Canada, and Mexico; and
WHEREAS, it is indeed exciting that the world's greatest sporting event is being
contested on American soil this summer; it is equally exciting that the State of Tennessee and
Metropolitan Nashville will play an important role in making the 2026 World Cup an event to
cherish and remember; now, therefore,
BE IT RESOLVED BY THE HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES OF THE ONE HUNDRED
FOURTEENTH GENERAL ASSEMBLY OF THE STATE OF TENNESSEE, THE SENATE
CONCURRING, that we honor and celebrate the Japan Men's National Team and Japan
Football Association for selecting the State of Tennessee and Metropolitan Nashville to host its
base camp and training site for the 2026 World Cup and extend to them our warmest welcome
to the Volunteer State and Music City USA.
BE IT FURTHER RESOLVED, that an appropriate copy of this resolution be prepared
for presentation with this final clause omitted from such copy and upon proper request made to
the appropriate clerk, the language appearing immediately following the State seal appear
without House or Senate designation.
